# Code Style

- TypeScript strict mode; explicit return types on all functions
- `async/await` over `.then()`; descriptive variable names
- Each function and React component in its own file when possible
- Object params (not positional args); params listed alphabetically
- JSDoc block above every function/component — no `@param`/`@returns`, TypeScript is the source of truth
- JSDoc comment above each param inline in the type

```typescript
/**
 * Does X for reason Y
 */
const myFunc = ({
  bar,
  foo,
}: {
  /** What bar represents */
  bar: number;
  /** What foo represents */
  foo?: string;
}): void => {};
```

- If the project has a test setup, write tests for new code
